## Germplasm Phenotype:
   - [smo4-1]()&nbsp;---&nbsp;Mild morphological phenotypes, with slightly dentate and pointed rosette leaves. defects in 18S and 5.8S rRNA maturation.
   - [smo4-1]()&nbsp;---&nbsp;Reduced size of aerial organs. Much shorter primary root length. Reduced numbers of cells in organs.
   - [smo4-2]()&nbsp;---&nbsp;Mild morphological phenotypes, with slightly dentate and pointed rosette leaves. defects in 18S and 5.8S rRNA maturation.
   - [smo4-3]()&nbsp;---&nbsp;Mild morphological phenotypes, with slightly dentate and pointed rosette leaves. defects in 18S and 5.8S rRNA maturation.
   - [smo4-4]()&nbsp;---&nbsp;Mild morphological phenotypes, with slightly dentate and pointed rosette leaves. defects in 18S and 5.8S rRNA maturation.
